<category term="Royal台北星期四文章" scheme="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewforum.php?f=3" label="Royal台北星期四文章"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=722&amp;p=750#p750"><![CDATA[
We will hold an on-site meeting only.<br /><br />摩斯漢堡明曜店(每人低消 :60元)<br />台北市仁愛路4段151巷37號地下室.<br />MRT忠孝敦化站3號出口 , 明曜百貨後方第二個巷子口<br /><br />Royal 台北 ( Thursday )<br />**** NEW***     Meeting time agenda:7:00-9:00 PM<br />7:00-7:30  Chatting time with your favorite drink, and introduction of the meeting by the host<br />7:30-8:00  discussion of the first topic<br />8:00-8:05  Take a group photo<br />8:05-8:30  discussion of the second topic<br />8:30-9:00  <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #800040">Individual Presentation</span></span> (each person will have two minutes to give a presentation on any topic of that day. <br />)<br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 1,</span> Trendy tips to organize your closet<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FotS0jkp_EO4SNUEvqj0OiiY2Mp2cprc/edit">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fot ... 2cprc/edit</a><!-- m --> <br /><br />1. According to the article, a well-organized closet means a lot to the start of whole day. Do you agree with that and why?<br />2. How to tidy up and store has become an important lesson now. Do you have your own principle to manage house storage and purchasing decision?<br />3. Besides the closet, do you have any experience to share about the space management in your house?<br />4. Is it easy to say goodbye to the stuff you don’t need in your opinion?<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 2,</span> The return of the liberal arts major<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gCM_GcBN97_oe6EvswOFXQTQd9wGYqkk/edit">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gCM ... GYqkk/edit</a><!-- m --><br />1. Artificial intelligence can’t be emphasized more recently. Do you agree with the view of this article that technology-related majors will continue to lose relevance?<br />2. Can you observe the different characteristics between people with tech and liberal arts degree in your working place or your personal experience?<br />3. What kind of jobs could most possibly be replaced by AI in near future?<br />4. After reading this article, will you encourage students in Taiwan to major in liberal arts?<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=55735">zoe</a> — Fri Apr 21, 2023 10:29 am — Replies 0 — Views 212</p><hr />
]]></content>
